    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1SignalConnection" kindref="compound">SignalConnection</ref> is the connection information held by the signal. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A signal can have zero to many connections, depending on how many slots are connected to this signal.</para>
<para>A connection contains:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1Callback" kindref="compound">Callback</ref> (slot)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1SignalObserver" kindref="compound">SignalObserver</ref> - interface provided by a slot owning object.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>It takes ownership of the callback, and will delete it when the connection is destroyed. @SINCE_1_0.0 </para>
    </detaileddescription>
